# Runtime Verification Standards

Implement runtime checks and verification scripts to catch integration issues before they reach production.

**Justification:** The "Open Editor" issue could have been caught earlier with proper runtime verification. This rule ensures critical integrations are verified at startup and during development.

## 🎯 Single Responsibility
This rule ONLY covers runtime verification patterns and startup checks. Not unit testing (see unit-testing) or E2E testing (see playwright-automation-standards).

## 📋 Implementation Checklist

### Runtime Verification Requirements
```markdown
- [ ] Create verification scripts for critical integrations
- [ ] Run pre-flight checks before application startup
- [ ] Add runtime assertions in development mode
- [ ] Log verification results clearly
- [ ] Fail fast on critical verification failures
- [ ] Provide actionable error messages
- [ ] Include verification in CI/CD pipeline
- [ ] Create developer-friendly verification commands
```

## 🔍 Verification Script Pattern

### Structure
```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node

/**
 * Verification script for [Feature Name]
 * 
 * This script verifies that [what it verifies]
 * to prevent [what issues it prevents].
 */

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');

console.log('🔍 Verifying [Feature Name]...\n');

let allPassed = true;
const results = [];

// Test 1: Check critical file/configuration
console.log('📋 Test 1: [Test Description]');
try {
  // Verification logic
  const passed = checkSomething();
  
  if (passed) {
    console.log('✅ PASS: [Success message]');
    results.push({ test: 'Test 1', status: 'PASS' });
  } else {
    console.log('❌ FAIL: [Failure message]');
    results.push({ test: 'Test 1', status: 'FAIL' });
    allPassed = false;
  }
} catch (error) {
  console.log('❌ ERROR:', error.message);
  results.push({ test: 'Test 1', status: 'ERROR' });
  allPassed = false;
}

// Summary
console.log('\n📊 Summary:');
results.forEach(r => {
  console.log(`${r.status === 'PASS' ? '✅' : '❌'} ${r.test}: ${r.status}`);
});

if (!allPassed) {
  console.error('\n⚠️ Some verifications failed!');
  process.exit(1);
}

console.log('\n🎉 All verifications passed!');
```

## 🚀 Startup Integration

### Pre-flight Checks
```javascript
// In startup script (e.g., start-with-feature.cjs)
async function runPreFlightChecks() {
  console.log('🔍 Running pre-flight checks...');
  
  try {
    const result = execSync('node verify-feature.cjs', {
      encoding: 'utf8',
      stdio: 'pipe'
    });
    
    if (result.includes('All verifications passed')) {
      console.log('✅ Pre-flight checks passed!');
      return true;
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('❌ Pre-flight checks failed!');
    console.log('Continuing anyway, but feature may not work correctly...');
    return false;
  }
}

// Run before starting application
await runPreFlightChecks();
```

### Runtime Assertions
```javascript
class RuntimeVerifier {
  constructor(feature) {
    this.feature = feature;
    this.checks = [];
  }
  
  async verify(name, checkFn) {
    const start = Date.now();
    try {
      const result = await checkFn();
      const duration = Date.now() - start;
      
      this.checks.push({
        name,
        passed: result,
        duration,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
      });
      
      if (!result) {
        console.warn(`⚠️ [${this.feature}] Check failed: ${name}`);
      }
      
      return result;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`❌ [${this.feature}] Check error: ${name}`, error);
      this.checks.push({
        name,
        passed: false,
        error: error.message,
        duration: Date.now() - start
      });
      return false;
    }
  }
  
  report() {
    const passed = this.checks.filter(c => c.passed).length;
    const total = this.checks.length;
    
    console.log(`\n📊 ${this.feature} Verification Report:`);
    console.log(`Passed: ${passed}/${total}`);
    
    this.checks.forEach(check => {
      const icon = check.passed ? '✅' : '❌';
      console.log(`${icon} ${check.name} (${check.duration}ms)`);
      if (check.error) {
        console.log(`   Error: ${check.error}`);
      }
    });
    
    return passed === total;
  }
}
```

## 🧪 Verification Examples

### Bridge Communication Verification
```javascript
async function verifyBridgeCommunication() {
  const verifier = new RuntimeVerifier('Bridge Communication');
  
  // Check bridge exists
  await verifier.verify('Bridge function exists', async () => {
    return await page.evaluate(() => 
      typeof window.__bridge === 'function'
    );
  });
  
  // Check signature
  await verifier.verify('Bridge has correct signature', async () => {
    return await page.evaluate(() => 
      window.__bridge?.length === 2
    );
  });
  
  // Check not overridden
  await verifier.verify('Bridge not overridden', async () => {
    const original = await page.evaluate(() => 
      window.__bridge?.toString()
    );
    
    // Inject potential override
    await page.evaluate(() => {
      // This should NOT override
    });
    
    const after = await page.evaluate(() => 
      window.__bridge?.toString()
    );
    
    return original === after;
  });
  
  return verifier.report();
}
```

### UI Component Verification
```javascript
async function verifyUIComponents() {
  const verifier = new RuntimeVerifier('UI Components');
  
  await verifier.verify('Overlay exists', async () => {
    return await page.evaluate(() => 
      !!document.getElementById('__overlay__')
    );
  });
  
  await verifier.verify('All buttons present', async () => {
    const buttons = await page.evaluate(() => {
      const overlay = document.getElementById('__overlay__');
      return overlay?.querySelectorAll('button').length;
    });
    return buttons === 5; // Expected number
  });
  
  await verifier.verify('Event handlers attached', async () => {
    return await page.evaluate(() => {
      const btn = document.getElementById('open-editor-btn');
      return btn?.onclick !== null;
    });
  });
  
  return verifier.report();
}
```

## 📊 Development Mode Checks

### Automatic Verification
```javascript
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  // Run verification every N minutes
  setInterval(async () => {
    console.log('\n🔍 Running periodic verification...');
    
    const results = await Promise.all([
      verifyBridgeCommunication(),
      verifyUIComponents(),
      verifyDataIntegrity()
    ]);
    
    if (results.some(r => !r)) {
      console.error('⚠️ Verification issues detected!');
      // Could trigger developer notification
    }
  }, 5 * 60 * 1000); // Every 5 minutes
}
```

### Console Helpers
```javascript
// Add verification commands to window in dev
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  window.__verify = {
    bridge: () => verifyBridgeCommunication(),
    ui: () => verifyUIComponents(),
    all: async () => {
      await verifyBridgeCommunication();
      await verifyUIComponents();
      console.log('Run window.__verify.report() for details');
    },
    report: () => {
      // Show detailed report
    }
  };
  
  console.log('💡 Verification available: window.__verify.all()');
}
```

## 🚨 Critical Verification Points

### Must Verify Before Production
```markdown
1. **Integration Points**
   - External API connections
   - Database connections
   - Message queue connections
   - WebSocket connections

2. **Security Features**
   - Authentication flow
   - Authorization checks
   - CSRF protection
   - Rate limiting

3. **Critical UI Features**
   - Payment flows
   - Data submission forms
   - File uploads
   - Real-time updates

4. **Data Integrity**
   - Schema migrations
   - Data transformations
   - Cache consistency
   - Event sourcing
```

## ✅ Verification Best Practices

```javascript
// ✅ Clear, actionable messages
console.log('❌ FAIL: Bridge function missing. Check if platform.setupBridge() was called before script injection.');

// ✅ Graceful degradation
if (!verificationPassed) {
  console.warn('Feature may not work correctly, but continuing...');
  // Enable fallback mode
}

// ✅ Detailed logging in verbose mode
if (process.env.VERBOSE) {
  console.log('Detailed verification steps...');
}

// ✅ Machine-readable output option
if (process.env.CI) {
  console.log(JSON.stringify(results));
}

// ✅ Quick verification command
// package.json
"scripts": {
  "verify": "node verify-all.cjs",
  "verify:quick": "node verify-critical.cjs"
}
```

## 📈 Success Metrics

- **Verification Coverage**: 100% of critical features have verification
- **Pre-flight Success Rate**: > 99% of startups pass verification
- **Early Detection**: Issues caught in development, not production
- **Clear Diagnostics**: < 1 minute to identify issue from verification
- **CI Integration**: All verifications run in CI pipeline

